\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 I\cb1 \
\
\cb3 Throughout the afternoon I watched them there,\cb1 \
\cb3 Snow-fairies falling, falling from the sky,\cb1 \
\cb3 Whirling fantastic in the misty air,\cb1 \
\cb3 Contending fierce for space supremacy.\cb1 \
\cb3 And they flew down a mightier force at night,\cb1 \
\cb3 As though in heaven there was revolt and riot,\cb1 \
\cb3 And they, frail things had taken panic flight\cb1 \
\cb3 Down to the calm earth seeking peace and quiet.\cb1 \
\cb3 I went to bed and rose at early dawn\cb1 \
\cb3 To see them huddled together in a heap,\cb1 \
\cb3 Each merged into the other upon the lawn,\cb1 \
\cb3 Worn out by the sharp struggle, fast asleep.\cb1 \
\cb3 The sun shone brightly on them half the day,\cb1 \
\cb3 By night they stealthily had stol\'92n away.\cb1 \
